      <prefercite id="aspace_beb8d0e2e2b4a504b159533890c83b98">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Louis Samuel Rothschild Papers. Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>
      </prefercite>
      <bioghist id="aspace_6714423e2f64d9547633d2bdbeffd561">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Louis Samuel Rothschild: born in Leavenworth, Kansas, on March 29, 1900; received a Ph.B., Yale University, 1920; business executive with Rothschild and Sons, Inc., Kansas City, Missouri, 1920-1956; chairman, Board of Inland Waterways Corporation, 1953-1959; chairman, Federal Maritime Board of U.S. Department of Commerce, 1953-1955; under secretary of commerce for transportation, 1955-1958; president or director of other corporations and government agencies.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_a248997b3400cf702f2e459e0d43fd92">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>Miscellaneous speeches and memoranda concerned with the public career of Louis S. Rothschild, particularly as under secretary of commerce for transportation in the Eisenhower administration.</p>
      </scopecontent>
